      "BookmanOldStyle-BoldItal",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      535.01,
      543.49,
      549.07
    ],
    "text": "However, if the opposing party objects to a document being admitted in",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      556.13,
      543.45,
      570.19
    ],
    "text": "evidence when it is first tendered, commonly two questions arise for",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      577.4,
      198.53,
      591.46
    ],
    "text": "determination.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      606.44,
      543.45,
      620.5
    ],
    "text": "Firstly, whether the document is authentic, in other words, if it is what the",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      627.56,
      543.45,
      641.62
    ],
    "text": "party tendering it represents it to be, and Secondly, whether, supposing it",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      648.68,
      543.45,
      662.74
    ],
    "text": "to be authentic, it constitutes legally admissible evidence as against the",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      669.92,
      343.51,
      683.98
    ],
    "text": "party who is sought to be affected by it.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      729.24,
      311.78,
      755.88
    ],
    "text": "4",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      72.0,
      543.46,
      86.06
    ],
    "text": "It is pertinent to observe that more than 65 years ago, Basnayake, C.J. in",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      93.12,
      543.67,
      107.18
    ],
    "text": "Mendis v. Paramaswami [62 N.L.R. 302 at 307] commended Section 154",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-BoldItal",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      114.24,
      543.48,
      128.3
    ],
    "text": "and more especially its explanation to all Judges of first instance in civil",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      135.48,
      509.86,
      149.54
    ],
    "text": "proceedings. Regrettably, the trial judge in this matter failed to do so.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      164.52,
      543.61,
      178.58
    ],
    "text": "In my view, there is a third, which in fact is the most fundamental, question",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      185.64,
      543.48,
      199.7
    ],
    "text": "which arises in terms of Section 136 of the Evidence Ordinance. That is",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      206.76,
      543.45,
      220.82
    ],
    "text": "whether the document proposed to be tendered in evidence is relevant in",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      228.0,
      312.79,
      242.06
    ],
    "text": "terms of the Evidence Ordinance.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      257.07,
      543.49,
      271.13
    ],
    "text": "Therefore, three issues arise for consideration by the trial judge when a",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      278.19,
      543.5,
      292.25
    ],
    "text": "document is sought to be tendered in evidence. They are; relevancy,",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      299.31,
      543.62,
      313.37
    ],
    "text": "admissibility and authenticity. All three must be determined by reference to",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      320.55,
      393.67,
      334.61
    ],
    "text": "the evidentiary rules in the Evidence Ordinance.\u201d",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      349.59,
      543.76,
      363.59
    ],
    "text": "Unfortunately, the learned trial Judge lost sight of the relevant provisions and",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      370.71,
      543.78,
      384.71
    ],
    "text": "made confusion worse confounded by making order that the objections will be",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      391.95,
      274.13,
      405.95
    ],
    "text": "considered in the final judgment.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      421.01,
      544.14,
      435.01
    ],
    "text": "Here again I am compelled to refer to the decision in Multiform Chemicals",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-BoldItal"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      442.25,
      357.67,
      456.25
    ],
    "text": "(Private) Limited. [supra. page 5] where I held:",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Bold",
      "BookmanOldStyle-BoldItal"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      471.29,
      543.62,
      485.35
    ],
    "text": "\u201cWhat is objectionable is the practice of moving that a document be marked",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      492.41,
      543.43,
      506.47
    ],
    "text": "subject to proof without specifying the matters on which proof is required.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      513.53,
      543.46,
      527.59
    ],
    "text": "Judges have become passive observers of such practice. This is not a",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      534.65,
      543.6,
      548.71
    ],
    "text": "healthy practice and more often than not, leads to additional issues as in",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      555.77,
      543.49,
      569.83
    ],
    "text": "this case. Moreover, it signifies a poor grasp of the relevant evidentiary",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      576.92,
      543.62,
      590.98
    ],
    "text": "principles. A trial judge must not condone such practices. There is a duty on",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      598.04,
      543.68,
      612.1
    ],
    "text": "a trial judge to inquire from the party moving that a document be marked",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      619.28,
      479.38,
      633.34
    ],
    "text": "subject to proof, what is required to be proved in the document.\u201d",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      729.24,
      311.78,
      755.88
    ],
    "text": "5",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      72.0,
      543.72,
      86.0
    ],
    "text": "Aggrieved by the said order, the Defendant sought and obtained leave to appeal",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      93.12,
      543.74,
      107.12
    ],
    "text": "from the High Court of the Southern Province (Exercising Civil Appellate",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      114.24,
      543.86,
      128.24
    ],
    "text": "Jurisdiction) holden in Galle. The High Court correctly set aside all orders which",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      135.36,
      543.93,
      149.59
    ],
    "text": "held that the objections of the Defendant to the marking of documents \u0db4\u0dd0.8 to",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "Iskoola Pota"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      156.84,
      435.22,
      171.07
    ],
    "text": "\u0db4\u0dd0.10 and \u0db4\u0dd0. 17 to \u0db4\u0dd0. 19 will be considered in the judgment.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "Iskoola Pota"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      186.12,
      313.75,
      200.12
    ],
    "text": "The High Court made further order that:",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      90.02,
      215.04,
      543.69,
      229.27
    ],
    "text": "(a) \u0db4\u0dd0. 8 should be allowed to be marked subject to proving its contents as it",
    "fonts": [
      "ArialMT",
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "Iskoola Pota"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      236.43,
      399.43,
      250.43
    ],
    "text": "is a statement made by the Plaintiff to the Police;",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      90.02,
      257.55,
      543.93,
      271.55
    ],
    "text": "(b) Court must hear parties, consider the pleadings and issues before any",
    "fonts": [
      "ArialMT",
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      278.67,
      354.55,
      292.9
    ],
    "text": "decision is made on \u0db4\u0dd0.9, \u0db4\u0dd0.17 and \u0db4\u0dd0.18.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "Iskoola Pota"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      90.02,
      299.91,
      543.75,
      314.14
    ],
    "text": "(c) Since \u0db4\u0dd0. 19 is a plan filed in a partition action instituted in the District",
    "fonts": [
      "ArialMT",
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "Iskoola Pota"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      321.27,
      543.86,
      335.27
    ],
    "text": "Court of Balpitiya, it should be allowed to be marked subject to the leading",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      342.39,
      543.68,
      356.39
    ],
    "text": "of evidence of the Registrar or a responsible officer on whether there was",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      363.51,
      543.91,
      377.51
    ],
    "text": "an appeal in that partition action or whether it is a fraudulent plan. Once",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      384.63,
      543.72,
      398.63
    ],
    "text": "such evidence is led, if that document is sought to be assailed, evidence",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      405.89,
      433.54,
      419.89
    ],
    "text": "should be called by the party assailing the said plan.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      434.93,
      543.85,
      448.93
    ],
    "text": "When trial re-commenced, the learned trial Judge held that there was no need",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      456.05,
      543.87,
      470.28
    ],
    "text": "to further prove documents marked \u0db4\u0dd0.9, \u0db4\u0dd0.17 and \u0db4\u0dd0.18. Reliance was placed",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "Iskoola Pota"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      477.29,
      543.93,
      491.29
    ],
    "text": "on the Civil Procedure Code (Amendment) Act No. 17 of 2022 (Act) which was",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      498.53,
      220.13,
      512.53
    ],
    "text": "certified on 23.06.2022.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      527.57,
      543.68,
      541.57
    ],
    "text": "It is against this order which the Defendant sought and obtained leave from",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      548.81,
      384.79,
      562.81
    ],
    "text": "Court. Hence, let me examine the Act in some detail.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      577.88,
      543.82,
      591.88
    ],
    "text": "The Act has two main provisions. Section 2 which inserts a new Section 154A to",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      599.0,
      543.73,
      613.0
    ],
    "text": "the Civil Procedure Code (CPC) and Section 3 which deals with transitional",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      620.24,
      143.54,
      634.24
    ],
    "text": "provisions.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      649.28,
      543.9,
      663.28
    ],
    "text": "There is a clear and important distinction between these two provisions as to",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      670.4,
      543.7,
      684.46
    ],
    "text": "their effective dates. Section 3 is qualified by the words \u201cNotwithstanding",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      691.51,
      543.42,
      705.58
    ],
    "text": "anything contained in section 2 of this Act, and the provisions of the Evidence",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      729.24,
      311.78,
      755.88
    ],
    "text": "6",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      72.0,
      544.06,
      86.06
    ],
    "text": "Ordinance, in any case or appeal pending on the date of coming into",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-BoldItal",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      93.12,
      543.89,
      107.18
    ],
    "text": "operation of this Act\u201d. This is an unequivocal statement by the legislature that",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-BoldItal",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      114.36,
      547.9,
      128.36
    ],
    "text": "these provisions have retrospective application to all pending cases and appeals.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
